Pre-Game Insights: Iqraam Rayners aims to score one or two goals in the international friendly for Bafana Bafana against Algeria.
Coach Hugo Broos has confirmed that Iqraam Rayners will start against Algeria at the Stade Nelson Mandela.
Rayners' performance in the DStv Premiership has been strong, with seven goals in 17 games, contributing to Stellenbosch FC's successful campaign.
Rayners is auditioning for a place in the Bafana squad for June’s World Cup qualifiers against Nigeria and Zimbabwe.
Khanyisa Mayo, another local-based striker, has struggled to make an impression at the international level.
Orlando Pirates’ Evidence Makgopa has managed to impress under coach Hugo Broos despite being injured currently.
Rayners will have a stronger combination around him compared to the experimental XI fielded against Andorra.
Algeria, under new coach Vladimir Petković, is also motivated to win back public support after their early exit from the Nations Cup.
